         <div class="documentTop SubjectPage">            
                     
            <h1>Sami policy</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/Upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_samepolitikk150x113.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">The state shall take steps to ensure that the Sami people can further develop and strengthen their own culture, their own language and their own business and industry and community life.</p>
            <img src="/Upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_samepolitikk150x113.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>The basis for the Government’s Sami policy is that, as a state, Norway was established on the territories of two peoples, Norwegians and Sami, and that both these peoples have the same right to develop their cultures and languages. Consideration of Sami interests shall be included in the development of policies in relevant areas. The Government shall also contribute to the development of international policy on indigenous peoples and cooperate on Sami issues with the Nordic countries.</p></div>
	    <div style="clear:both"></div>
	      
         </div>
         
         
                                
        
        
        
                            
    <div id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_divPageContent" class="documentBody">  
                

<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_grunnlaget100x75.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/midtspalte/the-foundation-for-sami-policy.html?id=87039">The foundation for Sámi policy</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               National laws and international conventions set the obligations towards the Sami population
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_ansvarsford100x75.jpg" alt="SamepolitikkFoto: Kenneth Hætta" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/midtspalte/division-of-responsibility-and-coordinat.html?id=86932">Division of responsibility and coordination</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               The Ministry of Government Administration, Reform and Church Affairs has overriding responsibility for coordinating Sámi matters.
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    


<div class="ArticleView">
        <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_konsultasjoner100x75.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" class="ArticleImg" />
        
        
        <div class="ArticleImgContent">
            <h2><a href="/en/dep/fad/Selected-topics/Sami-policy/midtspalte/consultation-duty-in-sami-matters.html?id=86931">Consultation duty in Sámi matters</a></h2>        
                
            <p>
               As an indigenous people, the Sámi are entitled to be consulted on matters that affect them, this right is enshrined in ILO Convention no. 169 on Indigenous and Tribal Peoples in Independent Countries, Article 6. The Agreement on procedures for consultations between the Central Government authorities and the Sámediggi sets out detailed procedures for how consultations with the Sámediggi shall take place. 
            </p>
            
        </div>
    </div>
    
    

